{"type":"message","id":"befce03b","parentId":"acf994ff","timestamp":"2026-03-03T05:45:57.103Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I can see the session status. Now I need to help the user configure the model in OpenClaw. Since I don't have direct file access tools (exec, read), I need to work with what's available.\n\nLooking at the user's request more carefully - they want to:\n1. Add a model configuration to OpenClaw\n2. The configuration was previously in Claude Code\n3. They want me to test it after configuration\n\nThe configuration uses a custom Anthropic-compatible endpoint (DashScope Aliyun) with various model mappings.\n\nFor OpenClaw, model configuration is typically done through:\n1. Environment variables in the shell/profile\n2. OpenClaw config files\n3. CLI commands like `openclaw config set`\n\nSince I can't directly execute commands or read files, I should use sessions_send to communicate with a session that can handle configuration, or provide the user with instructions.\n\nActually, let me try using sessions_send to send a configuration request to the control UI session or create a sub-agent to handle this. But first, let me check what sessions are available.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3864597393e54b5da69874d0","name":"sessions_list","arguments":{"limit":10}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qwen-portal","model":"coder-model","usage":{"input":9353,"output":492,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":9845,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772516751700}}
